You should do the multiplication before the division, using a larger type if there will be overflow.

    a = (int)((long long)b * d / c);

If you are doubtful about the sequence of operations you can parenthesise it

    a = (int)(((long long)b * d) / c);

although it is unnecessary, because although `*` and `/` have the same precendence they are parsed from left to right.

If you want to round the result you can add (or subtract if negative product) half the divisor before dividing.

    a = (int)(((long long)b * d + (c &gt;&gt; 1)) / c);

